[{"id":"VH987788","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH944227.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which choice best expresses the change in the speaker during the course of the poem?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH987788_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<p class=\"lead_in\"><span class=\"compose_cluster_phrase type:ordinal\"></span> Read the following poem carefully before you choose your answers.</p>\n\n<p class=\"introduction passage-intro\">The speaker in this poem is a tourist visiting the Italian city of Palermo.</p>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"poetry style:1\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\">Palermo</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">1&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>It was foolish of us to leave our room.</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>The empty plaza was shimmering.</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>The clock looked ready to melt.</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>The heat was a mallet striking a ball</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">5&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>and sending it bouncing into the nettles<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">1</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">prickly plants</span></span> of summer.</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Even the bees had knocked off for the day.</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>The only thing moving besides us</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>(and we had since stopped under an awning)</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>was a squirrel who was darting this way and that</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">10&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>as if he were having second thoughts</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>about crossing the street,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>his head and tail twitching with indecision.</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>You were looking in a shop window</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>but I was watching the squirrel</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">15&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>who now rose up on his hind legs,</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>and after pausing to look in all directions,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>began to sing in a beautiful voice</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>a melancholy aria<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">2</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">song traditionally included in an opera</span></span> about life and death,</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>his forepaws clutched against his chest,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">20&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>his face full of longing and hope,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>as the sun beat down</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>on the roofs and awnings of the city,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>and the earth continued to turn</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>and hold in position the moon</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">25&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>which would appear later that night</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>as we sat in a caf√©</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>and I stood up on the table</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>with the encouragement of the owner</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>and sang for you and the others</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">30&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>the song the squirrel had taught me how to sing.</span></div>\n<span class=\"mandatory_credit_block\"><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\">\"Palermo,\" Billy Collins, Penguin Random House and Macmillan, 2013.</span></span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">He experiences an imaginative transformation of reality.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">He uses desperate measures to gain attention.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">He indulges in a witty fantasy about Italian opera.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">He grows from cowardice to confidence.</p>"],"answer":0}]